---
description: Error handling rules for the application to ensure robust and user-friendly error management.
alwaysApply: false
---
- All thrown errors must include a unique error code and a user-friendly message.
- Use a global error handler for API routes and server actions.
- Log errors with contextual metadata (user ID, request ID, etc.).
- All user-facing error messages must be actionable and avoid technical jargon.
- Implement robust error handling and logging mechanisms.
- Provide clear and user-friendly error messages to the end-users.
- Consider using custom error types for consistent error handling.